Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with evolutionary algorithms for optimization problems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper analyzes the weighted vertex cover problem and proposes algorithms with respect to its optimal solution.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes multi-objective evolutionary algorithms for optimization problems.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes approximation algorithms for optimization problems.
